                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v-2</locus>
                           <desc>r: Recipe against leprosy.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: ቆለቈል፡ በሸኮኮ፡ ኩስ፡ ለዊሶ፡ በጥቶ፡ ይዱል፡ በ፫ቀን፡
                              ይቀረፍ፡ የዝብ፡ ምርኩዝ፡ ብሳና፡ ቅርፍታቸው፡ አለ፡ ወሐ፡ ቀጥቅጠሕ፡ ፫ቀን፡ አድርቆ፡ ደቁሰ፡ በጓት፡ ወይ፡
                              በጠላ፡ ይጠጣ፡ የደዌ፡ ሥጋ፡ ነው።…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same crude hand as Additio 8, in Amharic. Recipe
                              how to prepare a medicine against leprosy (yägäwe śǝga 'sickness of
                              the skin'). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer against wild animals and evil people. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>: ዡራዡር። በሰመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ የሊይ፡ ዡራማ፡ ዓመተ፡
                              ዡራዡር፡ ጨቆራን፡ አሌ፡ ለክሙ፡ በወራባ፡ በወራጋ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a crude hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#48r">f. 48r-49</locus>
                           <desc>v: Excerpt from Malkǝʾa Śǝllāse (ChRep 191, n</desc>
                           <locus target="#20">20</locus>).<quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#48r">48r</locus>: ሰላም፡ ለእኅቲክሙ፡ እለ፡ እሕዛ[sic]፡ አለመ።
                              ደሕራዊያን፡ ሥላሴ፡ እለ፡ ነበርክሙ፡ ቅድመ፡ ውሰተ፡ ልየ፡
                              አዝንሙ፡… </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Written in a crude hand. The text starts with
                           strophe 28 of the Malkǝʾa Śǝllāse (ChRep 191, n<locus target="#20">20</locus>
                           <note>). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#49v">f. 49v</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from Säʿatat za-lelit (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#49v">49v</locus>: እሴብሕ፡ ጸጋኪ፡ እግዚእትየ፡ ማርያም፡
                              እድ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a crude hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#49v">f. 49v</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from Malkǝʾa ʾIyasus (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#49v">49v</locus>: በሰመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ። ጥኡመ፡ ሰሞ፡
                              …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a crude hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#107v">f. 107v-108</locus>
                           <desc>v: ʾAsmat-prayer.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The text is hardly legible due to faded ink. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#110r">f. 110r-10</locus>
                           <desc>v: ʾAsmat-prayer</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#110r">110r</locus>: አሻቢ፡ አሸብሻቢ፡ ሳለ፡ በሕይውቱ፡ ቢሞት። ለበክቱ፡
                              እስኪፈረፍር፡ አእጽምቱ፡ ኢትልክፍ፡ ወኢታስለክፍ፡ ኢትንስክ፡ ወኢታሰነስክ፡ አለህ፡ ቃለ፡ አብ፡ ወውልድ፡
                              ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a crude hand in Amharic. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#110v">f. 110v</locus>
                           <desc>: ʾAsmat-prayer to help deliver the placenta without
                              problems.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#110v">110v</locus>: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወውልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፡
                              በስመ፡ አብ፡ ኲርኲርያኖስ፡ በስመ፡ ወልድ፡ ፍልፍልያኖስ፡ በስመ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሜልዮስ፡ በዝንቱ፡ ስምከ፡
                              ወበዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ እንግዲኅ፡ ልጅ፡ ውረድ፡ ይበለከ፡ አብ፡ ወውልድ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand as Additio 1. ʾAsmat-prayer to deliver
                              the placenta (ǝngǝdiḫ lǝğ "afterbirth") without problems. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes and pen trials throughout the Ms.
 - Pen
                           trail: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>: ሊተ፡ ተማኅፅኖ፡ ተማኅፀንኩ፡ በእግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡
                           ብሁተ፡ ሥልጣን። ተማኅፀንኩ፡ በ[sic].
 - Short passages have been erased
                           throughout the Ms.
 - Notes in upper margin have been erased: <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>, 4v, 5r, 5v.
 - A printed card of foreign
                           origin has been included into the filling of the left cover, it is a
                           business card(?) from the “Industria W &amp; I Peel”.
 - Printed
                           votive images of foreign origin are loosely placed after <locus target="#110">110</locus>. The first shows the Virgin and Child with a
                           prayer in French below. The second shows an image of the crucified Christ
                           on the one side and on the other side an obituary for Louis-Casimir Faye
                           in French.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings of Text VII are indicated by the
                              names of the days of the week written in the upper margin, in a
                              secondary hand: ዘሰኑይ: fols. 51r, 60v ዘሠሉስ: <locus target="#67r">fol.
                                 67r</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#73r">fol. 73r</locus> ዘሐሙስ:
                                 <locus target="#80r">fol. 80r</locus> ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#87r">fol. 87r</locus> ዘቀዳሚት: <locus target="#97r">fol. 97r</locus>
                              ዘሰንበት: <locus target="#102v">fol. 102v</locus> - Coloured threads have
                              been inserted in the right upper corner: fols. 11, 17, 25, 32 (white
                              thread), 37, 51, 60, 67, 73, 80, 87 (white thread), 97,
                           102.</desc>
                        </item>
